The paper discusses a theory of transformative discoveries in science that is derived from various fields such as philosophy of science, sociology of science, social network analysis, and information science. The paper also mentions the use of computational methods to study these networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Development), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
